Subscriptions

A new TV streaming service called Chef-TV has started in Chefland.

A group of N friends want to buy Chef-TV subscriptions. One subscription can be shared by 6 people, and the cost of one subscription is X rupees.

Determine the minimum total cost required so that all N friends can use Chef-TV.

Input Format
The first line contains an integer T, the number of test cases.
Each test case contains two integers N and X — the number of friends and the cost of one subscription.

Output Format
For each test case, print the minimum total cost required so that all friends can use Chef-TV.

import java.util.*;

class Codechef
{
    public static void main (String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception
    {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int t = sc.nextInt();

        while(t-- > 0){
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            int x = sc.nextInt();

            int subscriptions = n / 6;

            if(n % 6 != 0){
                subscriptions = subscriptions + 1;
            }

            int cost = subscriptions * x;
            System.out.println(cost);
        }
    }
}
